== Scottish Cup ==
Hibs will enter the [[Scottish Cup]] in the fourth round.

== Scottish League Cup ==
Having failed to qualify for [[UEFA|European]] competition in the previous season, Hibernian entered the [[Scottish League Cup]] at the second round, and were drawn to play [[Brechin City F.C.|Brechin City]], who were [[head coach|managed]] by former Hibs manager [[Jim Duffy (footballer)|Jim Duffy]].<ref>[http://sport.stv.tv/football/113820-brechin-boss-duffy-welcomes-cup-draw-against-old-side-hibs/ Brechin boss Duffy welcomes cup draw against old side Hibs], [[stv]], 4 August 2009.</ref> Hibs won the second round tie 3&ndash;0 on 26 August.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_cups/8220471.stm Hibernian 3&ndash;0 Brechin], [[BBC Sport]], 26 August 2009.</ref> In the third round, Hibs were again drawn to play at home, against [[Scottish Premier League|SPL]] newcomers [[St. Johnstone F.C.|St. Johnstone]].<ref>[http://www.hibs.co.uk/news/more.php?id=3658_0_1_0_C Co-Operative Cup 3rd Round], [[Hibernian F.C.]] official website.</ref> Hibs beat St. Johnstone 3&ndash;1 [[after extra time]] in the semi-final en route to their previous competition win in [[Scottish League Cup 2006-07|2007]]. Despite winning a league match against the same opponents on the previous Saturday, Hibs lost 3&ndash;1 to exit the competition.

